    "created_at": "2015-07-14T13:02:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-14T13:02:26Z",
    "body": "At the moment, there is also no way to update a tray menu item label, without recreating the tray menu, but this causes the tray menu to disappear if the user has it open so there is no way to give constantly updating status information via the tray menu at the moment, e.g. \"Searching for networks...\", \"Found 3 networks...\" etc. while the user is watching.\n\nWould popContextMenu be a way to provide this? i.e. After recreating the tray menu, the tray menu would be hidden, but then popContextMenu could be called to keep it showing?\n"
  },
